Sansita Italic (Sansita-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-Italic', Everything looks good.

Sansita Bold (Sansita-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-Bold', Everything looks good.

Sansita Bold Italic (Sansita-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Sansita ExtraBold Regular (Sansita-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Sansita ExtraBold Regular (Sansita-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sansita' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Sansita ExtraBold'.

Pass

Sansita ExtraBold Italic (Sansita-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'Sansita-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Sansita ExtraBold Italic (Sansita-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sansita-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sansita' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Sansita ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Sansita Black Regular (Sansita-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sansita' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Sansita Black'.

NID 6 is 'Sansita-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Sansita Black Italic (Sansita-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sansita' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Sansita Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass
